## Building a Nested Comments Widget in React

**Mental model:** Comments are a tree: each node has `id`, `text`, and `replies[]`. Render it with a recursive component. Adding a reply means finding the target node by id and appending a child — return a *new* tree so React re-renders. Recursion handles arbitrary depth.

### Step 1 — Tree shape + recursive render
```jsx
function Comment({ node, onReply }) {
  return (
    <div style={{ marginLeft: 16 }}>
      <p>{node.text}</p>
      {node.replies.map((r) => <Comment key={r.id} node={r} onReply={onReply} />)}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Step 2 — Immutable insert by id
Recurse, copying only the path to the target.

```jsx
const addReply = (nodes, parentId, text) =>
  nodes.map((n) =>
    n.id === parentId
      ? { ...n, replies: [...n.replies, { id: uid(), text, replies: [] }] }
      : { ...n, replies: addReply(n.replies, parentId, text) }
  );
```

### Step 3 — Per-node reply box
Track which node's reply box is open (one at a time is simplest).

```jsx
const [openId, setOpenId] = useState(null);
```

### Step 4 — Commit a reply
```jsx
const submit = (parentId, text) => { setTree((t) => addReply(t, parentId, text)); setOpenId(null); };
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Deep nesting | Recursion handles any depth; cap indent visually. |
| Empty reply | Trim and ignore. |
| Performance | Copying only the path (not the whole tree) keeps updates cheap. |

**Interview tip:** The recursive immutable-insert (copy just the path to the parent) is the core — note that returning a new tree is what lets React diff efficiently, and that you could swap the array for a normalized `byId` map at scale.

